You are working on a Healthcare Appointment Mobile System - a university group project.

Read CLAUDE.md for full project context, conventions, and module ownership.

Key rules:
- TypeScript strict mode everywhere
- Backend: Express + Prisma + PostgreSQL. Pattern: Controller → Service → Prisma
- Mobile: React Native Expo + Expo Router + React Native Paper + Zustand
- API responses: { success: true, data } or { success: false, error: { code, message } }
- Validate with Zod on backend, never trust client input
- Use named exports, kebab-case files, PascalCase components
- Each module has: controller.ts, service.ts, routes.ts, dto.ts, types.ts
- Never add Co-Authored-By to commits
- Commit with the correct team member's git identity based on module ownership (see CLAUDE.md)
- iOS 26 Liquid Glass: use NativeTabs (expo-router/unstable-native-tabs) for tab bar, GlassCard for cards. Never use Tabs from expo-router. See CLAUDE.md for full guide.
